title: Kate Herlihy Earns WBCA All-America Honorable Mention
text:
Kate Herlihy Earns WBCA All-America Honorable Mention
GLASSBORO, NJ – Rowan senior Kate Herlihy was named a WBCA All-America Honorable Mention on the organization’s 2024-25 team. Herlihy becomes the first Prof to earn All-America honors since 2016. The senior guard finished her career being named to the All-NJAC First Team this year, after earning Honorable Mention in 2024. She led the NJAC scoring (18.4 ppg) and topped the Profs in three-pointers made (58), assists (62), and steals (53) after starting all 26 games, averaging 28 minutes per contest.
